Sentencas: Using solid-phase reaction process to synthesize La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-delta (LCC) primary powder, composite hollow fiber membrane of NiO/LCC (1:1) was prepared by phase-conversion spinning method and then sintered at 1400 degrees C in air as micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC) support.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of composite support NiO/La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-δ by phase-conversion spinning method for micro-tubular SOFC

Sentencas: The particle size distribution, TG-DTA thermal analysis, structure, morphologies, electrical conductivity, thermal expansion and bending strength were characterized by laser particulate size analyzer, thermal analyzer, X-ray diffraction, scanning electron microscopy, standard DC four-probe technique, thermal expansion dilatometer and universal material testing machine.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of composite support NiO/La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-δ by phase-conversion spinning method for micro-tubular SOFC

Sentencas: Results indicate that LCC and NiO powders have considerable chemical and sintering compatibilities at SOFC co-firing temperature (1400 degrees C).
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of composite support NiO/La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-δ by phase-conversion spinning method for micro-tubular SOFC

Sentencas: The fracture section of the hollow fiber membrane exhibits a sandwich-like structure with homogeneous porous surfaces.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of composite support NiO/La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-δ by phase-conversion spinning method for micro-tubular SOFC

Sentencas: Two layers of obviously bigger parallel finger-like pores distribute uniformly between the inner and outer surfaces of the microtubule section.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of composite support NiO/La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-δ by phase-conversion spinning method for micro-tubular SOFC

Sentencas: The porosity of the sample is 60.6%, and increases to a relatively high value of 68.1% after reduction.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of composite support NiO/La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-δ by phase-conversion spinning method for micro-tubular SOFC

Sentencas: Electrical conductivity of the sintered specimen decreases as the temperature increasing in pure H-2.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of composite support NiO/La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-δ by phase-conversion spinning method for micro-tubular SOFC

Sentencas: The value reaches 10.8 S.cm(-1) at 700 degrees C. Bending strength before and after reduction are 39.6 MPa and 33.2 MPa respectively.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of composite support NiO/La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-δ by phase-conversion spinning method for micro-tubular SOFC

Sentencas: Thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) value of the NiO/LCC hollow fiber membrane gets to 12.4 x 10(-6) K-1, which is very close to that of other SOFC components, such as NiO/YSZ anode and LCC interconnect.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of composite support NiO/La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-δ by phase-conversion spinning method for micro-tubular SOFC
